Nollywood actor, Samuel Akinola who played the role of ‘Spiff’ in the Africa Magic family drama, The Johnsons have reacted to the death of Ada Ameh. DAILY POST reported that Ada Ameh passed away after she slumped on Sunday night. Her death has sent shock waves through the Nigerian movie and entertainment industry. The actress who had earlier publicly announced that she was battling depression after her daughter’s death was one of the favourite actors on the award-winning family show “The Johnsons” Reacting, Spiff took to his Twitter page writing: “ I’m really struggling to believe what I’ve been hearing of Aunty Ada Ameh’s demise. “Someone should pls tell me it is not true! On his Instagram, he also wrote: “Devastated.”